Program: Great Lives
Title: Sir Kyffin Williams
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00mbm3g
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 4 Sep 2009
Matthew Parris presents the biographical series in which his guests choose someone who has inspired their lives. Rolf Harris discusses the life of the Welsh painter Sir Kyffin Williams. Famous for his paintings inspired by the north Wales landscape, Williams never chose to be a painter; he was told by a doctor to take up art for his health when he was diagnosed with epilepsy. Prof Derec Llwyd Morgan joins the discussion. Show less